    • saveUniqueToken

      public MetaToken saveUniqueToken(Subject subject, String clientId, Boolean fetched, Instant expiryTime, boolean persistent)

      Returns:

    • createMetaToken

      public ClientPairInfoDTO createMetaToken(Subject subject, String clientId, boolean persistent) throws URISyntaxException, MalformedURLException, org.radarbase.auth.exception.NotAuthorizedException
      Creates meta token for oauth-subject pair.
      Parameters:
      subject - to create token for
      clientId - using which client id
      persistent - whether to persist the token after it is has been fetched
      Returns:
      ClientPairInfoDTO to return.
      Throws:
      URISyntaxException - when token URI cannot be formed properly.
      MalformedURLException - when token URL cannot be formed properly.
      org.radarbase.auth.exception.NotAuthorizedException

    • getMetaTokenTimeout

      public Duration getMetaTokenTimeout(boolean persistent, Project project)
      Gets the meta-token timeout from config file. If the config is not mentioned or in wrong format, it will return default value.
      Returns:
      meta-token timeout duration.
      Throws:
      BadRequestException - if a persistent token is requested but it is not configured.

    • removeStaleTokens

      @Scheduled(cron="0 0 0 1 * ?") public void removeStaleTokens()
      Expired and fetched tokens are deleted after 1 month.

      This is scheduled to get triggered first day of the month.
